frus:attachment.p:
The principles set forth in paragraphs 8 (a) and 9 of the recommendation relating to the Statute of the Free Territory of Trieste carry with them the following means of application: 1)
a) The Director of Security of the Territory will be appointed and can be recalled by the Governor after consultation with the Council of Government;
b) Security officials and police forces will be recruited and can be discharged by the Director of Security 2)
The Director of Security is in normal times subordinate to the Council of Government from which he receives instructions covering questions within his competence; 3)
Nevertheless a) the Governor will regularly receive reports from the Director of Security and will consult with him in regard to questions relating to his domain;
b) In taking part in the meetings of the Council of Government the Governor will be informed of instructions given to the Director of Security and can express his opinion on this subject;
c) In matters which affect his responsibilities (observation of the Statute, maintenance of public order and security and respect for human rights) the Governor can prevent the entry into force or the retention in force of any administrative measures. In a like manner he may propose measures of the same nature to the Council of Government; 4)
When he considers that exceptional circumstances endanger the independence of or the security of the Free Territory, public order or the respect of human rights, the Governor can order directly and require the execution of all necessary measurements subject to immediate
reference to the Security Council. In the same conditions he can himself if he considers it necessary take over the direction of the security services.
